commit.message: Version bump for 0.14.0
Update signing key link
Remove Python 2 incompatible arg for open() (introduced by 64fd7933793f5e6)
Update copyright year

Minor improvements
- Extension coverage increased
- Updated static check exclusions
- README testing update
- Stop using pypandoc/rst (use original README.md)

Fix decoding from file-like object reading too much data (#9)

- Decoder uses buffer if seeking possible, minimal reads otherwise
- Encoder/decoder buffers now unset/NULL after freeing (ext)
- Added test cases for successful and failing post-decode seek calls (ext)
- Add C extension coverage via Gcov + lcov
Fix DecoderException offset/position exposure (#10)
Fixed spelling errors in cli util
Version bump for release (0.13.0)

Fix _ubjson_decode_value case statement fallthrough

- Always goto bail on error
- Use correct check to not re-raise existing decoder DecoderException
Update CHANGELOG & version

Sort input file list

so that _ubjson.so builds in a reproducible way
in spite of indeterministic filesystem readdir order
and http://bugs.python.org/issue30461

See https://reproducible-builds.org/ for why this is good.

This PR was done while working on reproducible builds for openSUSE.
Minor static test related updates
Version bump for release (0.12.0)

Added Python 3.7 as supported version

- Tested with & without extension on Ubuntu 16.04 64-bit & 18.04 32-bit

Relax floating point type test case (for 32-bit targets)

- Otherwise fails due to imprecision around 32/64 float limits
Version bump for release (0.11.0)

Add object_hook parameter to decoder

- E.g. allows for custom types to be decoded

Add default param to encoder

- Allow for custom types to be encoded
Version bump for release (0.10.0)
Enable object key interning in conversion utility

Add object key interning support (PY3 only)

- Includes other minor updates
Minor to/from json utility improvements
